import{_ as t,o,c as r,a as s,d as e,e as a,b as n}from"./app-de7a4551.js";const c={},d=e("h1",{id:"hottest-temperature",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#hottest-temperature","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),a(" Hottest Temperature")],-1),i=n('<p>The National Weather Service&#39;s (NWS) measuring system recorded a temperature of 54.4 <code>Celsius</code> at Death <code>Valley</code> in eastern California on Sunday.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 美国国家气象局的测量系统周日在加州东部的死亡谷记录到了54.4摄氏度的温度。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> Celsius<br><code>英 [ˈselsiəs]美 [ˈselsiəs]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. （温度）摄氏的<br> n. 摄氏温度</p></blockquote><p>valley [ 复数 valleys ]<br><code>英 [ˈvæli]美 [ˈvæli]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 山谷；流域；溪谷<br> n. （Valley）人名；（英）瓦利；（法）瓦莱</p></blockquote></details><p>The temperature was recorded at 3:41 p.m. local time at <code>Furnace</code> <code>Creek</code> in Death Valley. In a statement, the NWS said, &quot;If <code>verified</code>, this will be the hottest temperature officially verified since July of 1913, also at Death Valley. As this is an extreme temperature event, the recorded temperature will need to <code>undergo</code> a formal review.&quot;</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 这个温度是当地时间下午3：41分在死亡谷的熔炉溪记录的。国家气象局在一份声明中表示：“如果得到证实，这将是1913年7月以来官方证实的最高温度，上一次最高温度也是在死亡谷。由于这是极端温度事件，因此所记录的温度将需要进行正式审核。”</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> furnace [ 复数 furnaces ]<br><code>英 [ˈfɜːnɪs]美 [ˈfɜːrnɪs]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 火炉，熔炉</p></blockquote><p>creek [ 复数 creeks ]<br><code>英 [kriːk]美 [kriːk]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 小溪；小湾</p></blockquote><p>verify ( verifying, verified, verifies )<br><code>英 [ˈverɪfaɪ]美 [ˈverɪfaɪ]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 核实，查证；证明，证实</p></blockquote><p>undergo ( undergoing, underwent, undergone, undergoes )<br><code>英 [ˌʌndəˈɡəʊ]美 [ˌʌndərˈɡoʊ]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 经历，经受</p></blockquote></details><p>The World <code>Meteorological</code> Organization (WMO) says the record for the highest temperature was 56.7 Celsius set on July 10, 1913 in Death Valley. And the highest temperature for the Eastern <code>hemisphere</code> was set in July 1931 in Kebili, Tunisia, at 55.0°C. However, the WMO notes that weather <code>historians</code> have questioned the accuracy of these old temperature records.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 世界气象组织表示，最高气温记录是1913年7月10日在死亡谷创下的56.7摄氏度。东半球的最高温度是1931年7月在突尼斯的基比利创下的55.0摄氏度。然而，世界气象组织表示，天气历史学家对这些年代久远的温度记录的准确性提出了质疑。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> meteorological<br><code>英 [ˌmiːtiərəˈlɒdʒɪk(ə)l] 美 [ˌmiːtiərəˈlɑːdʒɪk(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 气象学的</p></blockquote><p>hemisphere [ 复数 hemispheres ]<br><code>英 [ˈhemɪsfɪə(r)] 美 [ˈhemɪsfɪr]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. （地球的）半球；脑半球；（球体的）一半</p></blockquote><p>historian [ 复数 historians ]<br><code>英 [hɪˈstɔːriən] 美 [hɪˈstɔːriən]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 历史学家，史学工作者</p></blockquote></details><p>The organization said Monday on the social media service Twitter that it also will <em>work to</em> verify Sunday&#39;s <code>measurement</code>.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 该组织周一在社交媒体网站推特上表示，它也将努力验证周日所记录的这次温度的测量标准。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> work to -&gt; 努力实现：为了达到某个目标或完成某项任务而付出努力。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> measurement [ 复数 measurements ]<br><code>英 [ˈmeʒəmənt]美 [ˈmeʒərmənt]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. （通常以数字形式呈现的）测量结果；三围，（身材）尺寸；测量，计量；测量单位，度量制</p></blockquote></details><p>The U.S. National Park Service says Death Valley is &quot;famous as the hottest place on earth and <code>driest</code> place in North America.&quot; The <code>desert</code> area also includes Badwater <code>Basin</code>, the lowest point in North America at 85.9 meters below sea level. During the summer, the heat is <code>trapped</code> by the high valley walls and heated even more by the air pressure at its low point.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 美国国家公园管理局表示，死亡谷作为地球上最热的地方，也是北美最干燥的地方而闻名。这片沙漠地区还包括北美最低点恶水盆地，其海拔低于海平面85.9米。在夏季，热量被高高的山谷壁围困住，并在其最低点被气压加至更热。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> dry ( drying, dried, dryer, dries, driest )<br><code>英 [draɪ]美 [draɪ]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 干裂；干燥(状态)；干燥场；干季<br> adj. 干的；干燥的；雨少的；干旱的<br> v. （使）变干；（把…）弄干</p></blockquote><p>desert ( deserting, deserted, deserts )<br><code>英 [ˈdezət]美 [ˈdezərt]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 沙漠，荒漠；荒凉的地方；应得的赏罚<br> v. 离弃，舍弃（某地）；抛弃，遗弃（某人）；背弃，放弃；擅离，开小差；突然丧失<br> adj. 无人居住的，荒凉的；像沙漠的</p></blockquote><p>basin<br><code>英 [ˈbeɪs(ə)n]美 [ˈbeɪs(ə)n]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 盆；洗涤槽；流域；盆地，海盆；内港，内湾</p></blockquote><p>trap ( trapping, trapped, traps )<br><code>英 [træp]美 [træp]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. （捕捉动物的）陷阱；圈套；诡计；牢笼<br> v. 使落入险境；使陷入困境；卡住；夹住</p></blockquote></details><p>Visitors are warned to drink at least 4 <code>liters</code> of water each day and to carry additional water in their cars. They are also warned to stay close to their <code>vehicles</code> and watch themselves and others for <code>dizziness</code>, <code>nausea</code> and other signs of heat illness.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 游客被告知每天要至少喝4升水，并在车上携带额外的水。他们还被告知不要远离车辆，并注意自己与他人是否出现头晕、恶心和其它中暑的迹象。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> liter [ 复数 liters ]<br><code>英 [ˈliːtə(r)]美 [ˈliːtər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. [计量]公升（容量单位）<br> n. （Liter）人名；（英）利特</p></blockquote><p>vehicle<br><code>英: [ˈviːɪk(ə)l] 美: [ˈviɪk(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 车辆；工具；交通工具</p></blockquote><p>dizziness<br><code>英 [ˈdɪzinəs]美 [ˈdɪzinəs]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 头晕；头昏眼花</p></blockquote><p>nausea<br><code>英 [ˈnɔːziə]美 [ˈnɔːziə]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 恶心，呕吐感；极端的憎恶</p></blockquote></details>',12);function l(p,u){return o(),r("div",null,[d,s(" 美国死亡谷录得百年以来最高温度 "),i])}const h=t(c,[["render",l],["__file","25-hottest-temperature.html.vue"]]);export{h as default};
